Net result: The remastered early‑’60s Beatles LP best satisfies my core criteria — single‑artist, start‑to‑finish sequencing; warm analogue character with preserved dynamics and transients; concise melody‑first songs with close, integrated harmonies and restrained arrangements — so I choose it over the Queen Greatest Hits compilation.

