- The Very Best Of Fleetwood Mac (candidate 1): The description states a tightly curated remaster that preserves warm analogue headroom, tape‑like transient snap and microdynamics; piano‑and‑guitar‑forward arrangements; intimate close‑mic lead vocals; intelligible multi‑part harmonies; restrained overdubs and LP‑style sequencing that rewards start‑to‑finish listening. Those features directly match my core preferences: single‑artist, curated greatest‑hits that play like an album; preserved dynamics and analogue warmth; vocal presence and layered harmonies with space; restrained overdubs and sequencing that support narrative flow.
