- Tradeoffs where candidate 2 could have appealed: Candidate 2 does match my enjoyment of concise mid‑tempo, groove‑forward tracks with punchy drums and stacked harmonies, but those positives are outweighed by its radio‑ready mastering approach and emphasis on front‑of‑mix vocal presentation — both of which risk the hyper‑compression and loss of warm analogue dynamics I explicitly dislike.
- Conclusion: Because preserving microdynamics, analogue warmth, intimate lead presence, harmonies with space, and album‑style sequencing are central to my stated tastes — and Fleetwood Mac’s candidate specifically promises those attributes — The Very Best Of Fleetwood Mac is the clear fit. Candidate 2 offers some technical and stylistic elements I like (length and groove), but its radio‑ready polishing and likely compressed/mastered‑for‑singles approach conflict with my core dislike of hyper‑compressed, front‑of‑mix releases and its lack of an explicit LP‑style narrative sequencing makes it the weaker match.

